Here's the full implementation:

**XAML — wrap `CollectionView` in `RefreshView` for pull-to-refresh:**

```xml
<RefreshView IsRefreshing="{Binding IsRefreshing}"
             Command="{Binding RefreshCommand}">
    <CollectionView ItemsSource="{Binding Items}"
                    SelectionMode="Single"
                    SelectedItem="{Binding CurrentItem, Mode=TwoWay}"
                    SelectionChangedCommand="{Binding ItemSelectedCommand}">
        <CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
            <DataTemplate x:DataType="models:Item">
                <Grid Padding="12" ColumnDefinitions="48,*">
                    <Image Source="{Binding Icon}"
                           WidthRequest="40" HeightRequest="40" />
                    <Label Grid.Column="1"
                           Text="{Binding Name}"
                           VerticalOptions="Center" />
                </Grid>
            </DataTemplate>
        </CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
        <CollectionView.EmptyView>
            <ContentView>
                <Label Text="No items found."
                       HorizontalOptions="Center"
                       VerticalOptions="Center" />
            </ContentView>
        </CollectionView.EmptyView>
    </CollectionView>
</RefreshView>
```

**ViewModel — bindings and commands:**

```csharp
public partial class ItemsViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    private readonly IItemService _itemService;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private ObservableCollection<Item> _items = new();

    [ObservableProperty]
    private Item? _currentItem;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool _isRefreshing;

    public ItemsViewModel(IItemService itemService)
    {
        _itemService = itemService;
    }

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task ItemSelectedAsync()
    {
        if (CurrentItem is null) return;

        await Shell.Current.GoToAsync(
            $"{nameof(DetailPage)}",
            new Dictionary<string, object> { ["Item"] = CurrentItem });

        // Clear selection so the same item can be re-selected later
        CurrentItem = null;
    }

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task RefreshAsync()
    {
        try
        {
            var data = await _itemService.GetItemsAsync();
            MainThread.BeginInvokeOnMainThread(() =>
            {
                Items.Clear();
                foreach (var item in data)
                    Items.Add(item);
            });
        }
        finally
        {
            IsRefreshing = false; // MUST set to false to hide spinner
        }
    }
}
```

**Key binding summary:**

| Property | Binds to | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `ItemsSource` | `ObservableCollection<Item>` | Auto-updates UI on add/remove |
| `SelectedItem` (TwoWay) | `CurrentItem` | Tracks selected item |
| `SelectionChangedCommand` | `ItemSelectedCommand` | Navigates to detail page |
| `RefreshView.Command` | `RefreshCommand` | Reloads data from API |
| `RefreshView.IsRefreshing` | `IsRefreshing` | Controls spinner visibility |

**Important notes:**
- Use `ObservableCollection<T>`, never `List<T>` — otherwise the UI won't update.
- Set `IsRefreshing = false` in a `finally` block so the spinner always hides.
- Set `CurrentItem = null` after navigation so the same item can be tapped again.
- Set `x:DataType` on `DataTemplate` for compiled bindings.
- **Never use `ViewCell`** — use `Grid`, `StackLayout`, or any `View` as the template root.
